        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p>When a customer attempts to register with an invalid username (between 2 - 20 symbols), the system displays the correct validation message “<b>Username must be between 2 and 20 characters</b>”, but the error message is not aligned under the Username input field. This creates a UI inconsistency compared to other field error messages and may confuse users.</p>

<p><b>Steps to Reproduce:</b></p>

<ol>
	<li>Navigate to: <a href="http://localhost:8081/" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">http://localhost:8081/</a></li>
	<li>Click Login button in the top-right corner.</li>
	<li>Click the Register button. (tab)</li>
	<li>Enter valid values in <b>Email</b>, <b>First Name</b>, <b>Last Name and Phone number</b> fields.</li>
	<li>In the <b>Username</b> field, enter fewer than 2 symbols (1 symbol).</li>
	<li>Clicks the Register button.</li>
</ol>




<p><b>Expected Result:</b></p>

<ul>
	<li>Validation error message <b>“Username must be between 2 and 20 characters”</b> is displayed.</li>
	<li>The message is <b>left-aligned with the Username input field</b> and appears directly underneath it.</li>
	<li>Spacing, font size, and style match the other validation messages in the form.</li>
</ul>




<p><b>Actual Result:</b></p>

<ul>
	<li>Validation error message is displayed: <b>“Username must be between 2 and 20 characters”</b>.</li>
	<li>The message is <b>misaligned</b>, not properly positioned under the Phone Number input.</li>
	<li>UI looks inconsistent compared to other field errors.</li>
</ul>




<p><b>Severity:</b> Minor</p>
